atra's identity and her translation into theatre - converge to be (dis)solved by Shakespeare.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 4aCultural Studies. 4aHistory. 4aLate Middle Ages & Renaissance. 4aLiterary History and Criticism. 4aTheatre & Festivals. 7aHISTORY / Renaissance.2bisacsh  aCleopatra, Theatre, Gender, Otherness, Renaissance.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311066152108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2019 Englishz978311061036908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2019z9783110606348oZDB-23-DKU40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048537235zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048537235423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789048537235.jpg  a978-3-11-061036-9  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-066152-1  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2019  aZDB-23-DKUb2019